Ten people were killed and 64 injured in a  bus accident about 280 kilometres (175 miles) west of the capital Harare,  press reports said Tuesday
Police said the bus burst a front tyre, veered off the road and overturned  after it hit a tree in the accident Monday.
The dead include two women, believed to be returning from a church service  and a baby.
It was the second tragedy in less than two months involving buses carrying  rural commuters. Last month, 23 people died in another rural bus accident in  Mt Darwin, about 130 kilometres (80 miles) north of Harare.
